---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Base
  title="Corrections"
  description="Our public corrections log and the policy behind it. When we get something wrong, we fix it in the open."
>
  <div class="wrap prose" data-pagefind-body>
    <h1>Corrections</h1>
    <p>
      This page ships from day one. When we confirm we got something wrong, we
      fix it fast and we fix it visibly. We put a note on the corrected page and
      a dated entry here. We do not quietly change a substantive claim and
      pretend it was always that way.
    </p>

    <h2>How to report an error</h2>
    <p>
      If you think we got something wrong, tell us. Email
      corrections@carriersonnotice.com. Tell us the page and what you think is
      wrong. If you can, point us to a source.
    </p>

    <h2>What counts as a correction</h2>
    <p>
      A substantive correction changes a fact or a claim. It is not a typo or a
      small wording fix. Every substantive correction is logged below with a
      date. The full policy is on the
      <a href="/legal/corrections-policy">corrections policy</a> page.
    </p>

    <h2>Corrections log</h2>
    <div class="notice">
      <p>
        No corrections yet. This log is empty at launch. When we make a
        substantive correction, a dated entry appears here.
      </p>
    </div>

    <table class="data-table">
      <caption>Public corrections log</caption>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th scope="col">Date</th>
          <th scope="col">Page</th>
          <th scope="col">What changed</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td colspan="3">No entries yet.</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>
</Base>
